  <assign id="16">
    <name>Assignment #2:  Designing Activities that Require Depth of Knowledge</name>
    <intro>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;" face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;Watch a video on Webb's Depth of Knowledge. The video introduces Webb's Depth of Knowledge and provides examples for each level.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;" face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;&lt;a title="new website - opens in new window" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WMqKN7edRcU" target="_blank"&gt;video&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;" face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;Read the article &lt;a title="PDF - opens in new window - Cognitive Rigor article" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Cognitive_Rigor_Paper.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;Cognitive Rigor: Blending the Strengths of Bloom’s Taxonomy and Webb’s Depth of Knowledge to Enhance Classroom-Level Processes&lt;/a&gt; by Hess, Jones, Carlock, and Walkup. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;" face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;Read one of the following articles on applying Webb’s Depth of Knowledge levels in reading, social studies, writing, science, math:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;a title="PDF - Opens in new window - Depth of Knowledge - Reading" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/DOK_Reading.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;Reading&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;span face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a title="PDF - Opens in new window - Depth of Knowledge - Social Studies" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/DOK_SocialStudies.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;Social Studies&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;a title="PDF - Opens in new window - Depth of Knowledge - Writing" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/DOK-Writing.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;Writing&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;span face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a title="PDF - Opens in new window - Depth of Knowledge - Science" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/DOK_Science.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;Science&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;a title="PDF - Opens in new window - Depth of Knowledge - Math" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/DOK_Math.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;Math&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;" size="3"&gt;&lt;span face="Calibri"&gt;Write a one-page reflection on the Depth of Knowledge levels of the curriculum or assessment materials you currently are using in your classes. Consider in your reflection how you might ask questions or design activities to increase Depth of Knowledge levels. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;" size="3"&gt;&lt;span face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;Click below on "Add my submission" to submit your reflection.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: black; font-family: Arial; font-size: 6.5pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;" lang="EN"&gt;Above are some links to information provided by other organizations. These links are provided for the user's convenience. The U.S. Department of Education cannot guarantee the accuracy of the information at these sites. The inclusion of these links is not intended to reflect their importance; nor is it intended to endorse any views or products of these organizations. For further information, see our &lt;a href="http://www2.ed.gov/about/contacts/gen/othersites/edrespol.html" target="_blank"&gt;Collection Scope and Criteria for Inclusion&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</intro>
